						               													<description>One minute is not the world, right? Do you think so even if you have even less time to memorize every detail of an image? Memorace board game amusingly develops not only memory but also general knowledge and literacy. Learning becomes a captivating experience with its tasteful illustrations. How good is your memory?&amp;#10;&amp;#10;One of the great parts of the Memorace board game series is Magic Tales. The child can cross the threshold of the fairytale world, meet their favorite fairytale heroes and learn about new ones. Was the princess blonde or brown haired? What color was the ladybug? How many wolves stood with their backs to the picture?&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The point is that not the smallest detail escapes our attention and success is not left behind.&amp;#10;You can play Memorace alone or with more people.&amp;#10;1.Draw a card and put it in front of you!&amp;#10;2.Turn the clock over and try to memorize as many details as possible before the sand drips off - it&amp;rsquo;s about 10 seconds.&amp;#10;3. Throw the dice!&amp;#10;4.If you rolled 1, you must answer the thought-provoking puzzle on the front panel. Look at the picture and calculate or deduce correctly!&amp;#10;5.If you did not roll 1, turn the card over and answer the question on the back next to the rolled number. These will put your memory to the test, but if you watch well, you will know the answer for sure!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;There&amp;rsquo;s no reason to get frustrated even if you didn&amp;rsquo;t know the answer, turn the card over and find the solution! However, if you answered correctly, you can keep the card - congratulations, you already have a point!&amp;#10;Who will collect the most cards? Can you break your own record?&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
